The last four steps leverage our understanding how the underlying hardware really works in a modern microprocessor and collectively only requires 21 lines of C code. Figure~\\ref{fig:1.20} shows speedup on a log scale of a factor of nearly 50,000 over the original Python version. Instead of waiting almost six hours, it would take less than a second!

