\\section*{3.11 Historical Perspective and Further Reading}

This section surveys the history of the floating point going back to von Neumann, including the surprisingly controversial IEEE standards effort, plus the rationale for the 80-bit stack architecture for floating point in the x86. See the rest of \\textbf{Section 3.11} online.

