\\begin{enumerate}
    \\item An instruction is fetched from the instruction memory, and the PC is incremented.
    \\item A register $(\\times 2)$ value is read from the register file.
    \\item The ALU computes the sum of the value read from the register file and the sign-extended 12 bits of the instruction (offset).
    \\item The sum from the ALU is used as the address for the data memory.
    \\item The data from the memory unit is written into the register file $(\\times 1)$.
\\end{enumerate}

