\\begin{figure}[htbp]
\\centering
\\includegraphics[width=0.8\\textwidth]{_page_0_Figure_2.jpeg}
\\caption{Roofline Model [Williams, Waterman, and Patterson, 2009]. This example has a peak floating-point performance of 16 GFLOPS/sec and a peak memory bandwidth of 16GB/sec from the Stream benchmark. (Since Stream is actually four measurements, this line is the average of the four.) The dotted vertical line in color on the left represents Kernel 1, which has an arithmetic intensity of 0.5 FLOPs/byte. It is limited by memory bandwidth to no more than 8 GFLOPS/sec on this Opteron X2. The dotted vertical line to the right represents Kernel 2, which has an arithmetic intensity of 4 FLOPs/byte. It is limited only computationally to 16 GFLOPS/s. These data are based on the AMD Opteron X2 (Revision F) using dual cores running at 2GHz in a dual socket system.}
